snippet: A day after Indian soldiers shot dead two people in a car that did not stop at a checkpoint, angry crowds gathered in Kashmir, chanting slogans and throwing stones.
abstract: Protests break out in Indian-administered Kashmir one day after Indian soldiers opened fire on a car that did not stop at a checkpoint, killing two people.
lead_paragraph: A day after Indian soldiers shot dead two people in a car that did not stop at a checkpoint, angry crowds gathered in Kashmir, chanting slogans and throwing stones.

headline.main: Protests Erupt in Kashmir After Army Shooting
